metadata.name: Crooked Mirror
metadata.description:
I start my collection with "sinkholes". Receding salt water leaves behind underground salt deposits. Runoff from periodic rains dissolves the salt patches. Without support, land above collapses. Sometimes, they are filled with water afterwards. 
 
This enormous sinkhole looks like a crooked mirror. Above - human impact, drowning land. At reflection - nature ruins and devastation. 

Photo 5101  x  7652
Location - Dead Sea
Unique 1/1 NFT edition
